Important Considerations:

  • Price Sensitivity: Including price as an attribute is essential in conjoint analysis to determine how much consumers are willing to pay for different features.
  • Independence of Attributes: For accurate results, you need to ensure these attributes function independently in a consumer's mind. There might be some interaction (like base finish partially influencing the perceived value of a leather upgrade).
  • Manageable Levels: Too many levels per attribute can make the possible chair combinations overwhelming for respondents.
